  "name": "ethernetPacket::HasProtocolError",
  "category": "IP",
  "title": "ethernetPacket::HasProtocolError",
  "source": "chm_extract_v15/CANoeCANalyzer/Topics/CAPLFunctions/IP/Methods/CAPLfunctionHasProtocolError.htm",
  "syntax": [
    "word ethernetPacket.HasProtocolError();"
  ],
  "description": [
    "Returns 1, if the IP protocols of the Ethernet packet contains protocol errors, like wrong checksum or wrong length field, etc.Use ethernetPacket::GetProtocolErrorText to get a description of the error."
  ],
  "parameters": [],
  "return": "",
  "example": {
    "description": [],
    "code": "on ethernetPacket *\n{\n  if (this.hasProtocolError())\n  {\n    char text[100];\n    this.GetProtocolErrorText( text );\n    write( \"Protocol error on Eth %d: %s\", this.msgChannel, text );\n  }\n}"
  },
